Sometime very soon, we will shedding ourselves of the heavy coats and itchy jumpers. It will be a glorious day as we make our way in the world safe in the knowledge of a coming summer. However, this is the UK. Realistically, it doesn’t truly become shorts and T-shirt weather until July. Spring is unpredictable on this isle and our wardrobes must reflect that. Those in the fashion world call it a transitional period. In layman terms, this means it’s too warm for a coat but too chilly to walk around in short sleeves. So, how do you come to a middle ground? The answer is a blazer. The perfect ‘throw on and go’ piece, a blazer truly goes with everything. From Arket to ASOS, there are some great blazers available on the online high street. Neutrals are always a good place to start, so choose grey and beige for a staple addition to your wardrobe. If you prefer a pop of colour, go for pops of lime green and purple. While the weather remains on the chilly side, wear yours with a knit underneath and when the temperature rises, switch it out for a cool t-shirt. And so, to get your spring wardrobe off to the best start, here are nine of the best blazers to buy now. Get it for £135 at Arket Get it for £159 at Djerf Avenue Get it for £65 at River Island Get it for £89.99 at Zara Get it for £95 at & Other Stories Get it for £79.99 at Mango Get it for £74.95 at NA-KD Get it for £65 at River Island Get it for £49.99 at ASOS. This article contains affiliate links. We may earn a small commission on purchases made through one of these links but this never influences our experts’ opinions. Products are tested and reviewed independently of commercial initiatives. Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk. MORE : Where to shop or rent pre-owned Louis Vuitton as prices soar MORE : A tried and tested shopping guide to the latest foundation launches MORE : An expert reveals the best bedding for your sleep style